Master Answer:
Vaccines contain small amounts of specific ingredients (also called components), all of which play necessary and important roles during vaccine production. All of these ingredients are safe in the amounts used in vaccines, learn more here. If you want to know about a specific vaccine, the Canadian Immunization Guide lists all approved vaccines in Canada and their ingredients.
